[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":213},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows\u002F":189,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows\u002F":198},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190801\u002F449913843\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":171,"date":172,"description":173,"extension":174,"lang":175,"meta":176,"navigation":177,"path":178,"readingMinutes":179,"seo":180,"standalone":181,"stem":182,"tags":183,"tldr":186,"updated":186,"url":187,"__hash__":188},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows.md","The Term 'XXX' Is Not Recognized as the Name of a Cmdlet, Function, Script File, or Operable Program","8443993491",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":164},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,51,61,64,67,80,83,87,95,101,104,110,116,121,127,132,143,149,157,161],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Weird situation — no matter which package command I ran, I got \"The term 'xxx' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function, script file, or operable program.\" Here's a note on how to fully fix it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-problem","The problem",[17,25,26,27,34,35,39,40,43,44,43,47,50],{},"A few days ago I wrote a post on ",[28,29,33],"a",{"href":30,"rel":31},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fhexo\u002F20190730\u002F884035779\u002F",[32],"nofollow","Hexo commands stopped working (article in Mandarin)",". Today when I tried other ",[36,37,38],"code",{},"npm"," commands — ",[36,41,42],{},"vue cli",", ",[36,45,46],{},"express",[36,48,49],{},"koa"," — all of them produced:",[52,53,59],"pre",{"className":54,"code":56,"language":57,"meta":58},[55],"language-text","XXX : The term 'XXX' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function, script file,\nor operable program. Check the spelling of the name, or if a path was included,\nverify that the path is correct and try again.\nAt line:1 char:1\n+ XXX s\n+ ~~~~\n    + CategoryInfo          : ObjectNotFound: (XXX:String) [], CommandNotFoundExceptio\n   n\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : CommandNotFoundException\n","text","",[36,60,56],{"__ignoreMap":58},[17,62,63],{},"(XXX = whatever command you typed)",[17,65,66],{},"I tried these:",[68,69,70,74,77],"ul",{},[71,72,73],"li",{},"Uninstall Yarn (I'd installed Yarn the day before)",[71,75,76],{},"Uninstall Composer (I'd installed Composer the day before)",[71,78,79],{},"Reinstall Node.js",[17,81,82],{},"None of them worked. Here's the actual fix.",[12,84,86],{"id":85},"the-fix","The fix",[17,88,89,90,94],{},"Open Control Panel \u002F System and Security \u002F System, then click ",[91,92,93],"strong",{},"Advanced system settings",".",[17,96,97],{},[98,99],"img",{"alt":93,"src":100},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FvblSJcg.png",[17,102,103],{},"Then Advanced \u002F Environment Variables.",[17,105,106],{},[98,107],{"alt":108,"src":109},"Environment Variables","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FF5nIfHs.png",[17,111,112,113,94],{},"In System variables at the bottom, find ",[91,114,115],{},"Path",[17,117,118],{},[98,119],{"alt":115,"src":120},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FsNnUoeJ.png",[17,122,123,124,94],{},"Click ",[91,125,126],{},"Browse",[17,128,129],{},[98,130],{"alt":126,"src":131},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FOSBG361.png",[17,133,134,135,138,139,142],{},"Find your npm directory and point to it — usually ",[36,136,137],{},"C:\\Users\\username\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm"," (replace username with your username).\n(Mine for example: ",[36,140,141],{},"C:\\Users\\Hsiangfeng\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm",")",[17,144,145],{},[98,146],{"alt":147,"src":148},"Image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fe6gGNKT.png",[17,150,151,152,43,154,156],{},"Finally, reopen CMD or PowerShell — ",[36,153,42],{},[36,155,46],{},", any command will work.",[12,158,160],{"id":159},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,162,163],{},"Why did this happen? No idea — couldn't even find the cause. But it's fixed, so whatever.",{"title":58,"searchDepth":165,"depth":165,"links":166},2,[167,168,169,170],{"id":14,"depth":165,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":165,"text":23},{"id":85,"depth":165,"text":86},{"id":159,"depth":165,"text":160},"Nodejs","2019-08-01 10:28:33","Weird situation — no matter which package command I typed, I got \"The term 'xxx' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function, script file, or operable program.\" Here's a note on how to fully fix it.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows","2",{"title":6,"description":173},false,"en\u002FNodejs\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows",[184,185],"Node.js","Troubleshooting",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fcommand-not-recognized-as-cmdlet-windows\u002F","SFx0Te47O1PRgbypRlUkDfimlijWxGteY99GyH06SIw",{"newer":190,"older":194},{"url":191,"title":192,"date":193},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F01\u002Fvue-girlfriend-intermission\u002F","Build Yourself a Girlfriend with Vue! — Intermission","2019-08-01 10:54:29",{"url":195,"title":196,"date":197},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F31\u002Flaravel-vue-eslint-vscode-fix\u002F","Fixing ESLint Not Working Statically for Laravel-Vue in VSCode","2019-07-31 14:49:14",[199,203,208],{"url":200,"title":201,"date":202,"readingMinutes":179},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F","Tired of Opening Multiple Terminals to Run Commands? Use Concurrently","2026-01-13 09:45:28",{"url":204,"title":205,"date":206,"readingMinutes":207},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2025\u002F03\u002F